## 0. Session start
**New machine / second developer → [`SETUP.md`](SETUP.md)** (prerequisites, access, `.env`, verification, first run).
At the start of every session run **`/bootstrap`** ([`.claude/commands/bootstrap.md`](.claude/commands/bootstrap.md)) —
it loads the task playbook [`ai/rules/new-task-bootstrap.md`](ai/rules/new-task-bootstrap.md) + the GRACE map
[`grace/MODULE-INDEX.md`](grace/MODULE-INDEX.md), checks engine auth, and asks you to briefly summarize context.
**First thing, `/bootstrap` runs `bash ops/session-state.sh`** — a monitor over **both repos** (orchestration +
target {{PROJECT}}: branch, ahead/behind origin, dirty tree, whether `{{GRACE_PILOT}}` exists), the **{{TRACKER}}
tracker** (project `{{JIRA_KEY}}`; key in `.env`) and **GRACE / doc-freshness**. Always confirm you are on the
**current state** (pull the ticket, read canonical code if the local checkout lags, account for GRACE drift). Then
drive the task through taskctl, coming back to the user for decisions/brainstorm (`AskUserQuestion`).

