## 4. taskctl — how we work
- **Tracker = {{TRACKER}}**, project **`{{JIRA_KEY}}`** (creds in `.env`, gitignored, `JIRA_PROJECT_KEY={{JIRA_KEY}}`). The ticket in flight is named manually in-session. **Multi-user as equals:** each dev under their own `JIRA_EMAIL`/token, assignee not hardcoded; the owner adds equal-role members in {{TRACKER}}.
- Cycle: `frame → plan → plan-review → run (worktree) → review → audit → publish`. One engine plans/implements (claude), **another reviews** (codex) — two vendors' blind spots don't overlap.
- **How taskctl REALLY works in this project** → [`docs/taskctl.md`](docs/taskctl.md) (which stages hit the APPROVE gate, what `run --finalize` does / doesn't, whether transition/comment are enabled, exact engine argv).
- **codex call pattern** (read-only review, in background): `codex exec -s danger-full-access --skip-git-repo-check -c model_reasoning_effort=high -C "<dir>" "<prompt>" < /dev/null` (redirect stdin so it doesn't hang). The verdict is at the end of the log; do a failure-scan (5h-limit / rate-limit) before reading it.
- **Collaboration:** worktree is local (`<target>/.worktrees/<slug>`, gitignored, not committed). Code is shared **via branch + PR** into {{PR_TARGET}} (the protected branch `{{INTEGRATION_BRANCH}}` is never direct-pushed). State/plan/review artifacts under `ai/tasks/<id>/` are **committed to the shared orchestration repo** (both see one plan/review/stage). One ticket, one driver at a time. evidence-ledger: commands + timestamps + hashes/figures.

## 5. GRACE — status, AWARENESS and REFRESH  (grace.enabled = {{GRACE_ENABLED}})
- **The graph lives on branch `{{GRACE_PILOT}}`** (not merged into the integration branch, left that way) — modules + CrossLinks + contracts + verification + no-lookahead invariants. Authoring copy — `grace/xml/docs/`.
- **Awareness every session:** `/bootstrap` loads [`grace/MODULE-INDEX.md`](grace/MODULE-INDEX.md) (compact map: purpose/path/blast-radius) + [`grace/AI-BRIEF.md`](grace/AI-BRIEF.md) (discipline: find the module → blast-radius → contract → no-lookahead → trust code over docs). Full edges/contracts — `grace/xml/docs/*.xml`.
- **Freshness every session:** `bash grace/check-freshness.sh` (how far branch/graph/docs lag the code; MODULE-INDEX ↔ graph sync).
- **Refresh (what is auto vs gated):** *Deterministic* — rebase `{{GRACE_PILOT}}` on the integration branch, lint, regen `MODULE-INDEX.md` from the graph, drift flag. *Gated (not a blind hook)* — graph content (new modules/edges/contracts) via the cross-model `sync-grace` (Claude extracts → codex verifies) — "generator ≠ judge."
- **GRACE debt:** if a change touches modules/contracts/edges, record the delta and schedule `sync-grace` when you next touch those modules. Don't let the graph diverge from the code silently.
