## 9. Boundaries & security
- **Target `{{INTEGRATION_BRANCH}}` is protected** — work via per-task worktree → PR, never direct-push.
- **Secrets** — never in artifacts and never in git (only key names / the fact of access); **before every push to `{{INTEGRATION_BRANCH}}`**, secret-scan the staged diff.
- Codex logs carry harmless noise and codex can hit a **5h limit** — failure-scan the log before reading the verdict; `codex exec` hangs on open stdin → `< /dev/null`.
